Design Philosophy
Gig workers earn and think week-to-week. A monthly or annual premium model creates a psychological and cash-flow mismatch with how they live. GigShield's premium structure mirrors the gig economy's rhythm — simple, weekly, and auto-renewed every Monday.

Premium Calculation Formula
Weekly Premium = Base Rate × Zone Risk Multiplier × Season Multiplier × Tier Factor

Base Rate         = ₹25  (flat for all workers)
Zone Multiplier   = 0.8 (Low Risk) → 1.0 (Medium Risk) → 1.5 (High Risk/Flood-Prone)
Season Multiplier = 1.0 (Oct–May, dry/mild) → 1.3 (Jun–Sep, active monsoon)
Tier Factor       = 1.0 (Basic) | 1.7 (Standard) | 2.8 (Pro)

