Worked Example

Ravi — Standard Tier, Tambaram (high flood risk), October (monsoon)

₹25 (base) × 1.3 (high flood zone) × 1.3 (monsoon season) × 1.7 (Standard tier)
= ₹71.83 / week

If rain trigger fires on a Tuesday for 5 hours:
  daily_avg = ₹3,800 / 6 days = ₹633
  hourly_rate = ₹633 / 10 hrs = ₹63.3
  raw_payout = ₹63.3 × 5 hrs × 70% (rain payout %) = ₹221.6
  final_payout = min(₹221.6, ₹200 daily cap) = ₹200 ✅

Dynamic Pricing Features
Forecast-Based Weekly Adjustment
Each Monday when the premium renews, the AI engine checks the next 7-day weather forecast. If high disruption probability is detected, the premium adjusts upward — and workers are notified in advance.
Example:
  Forecast shows 3 days of heavy rain next week →
  Standard tier premium increases from ₹57 → ₹68 for that week
  Worker notified: "Higher disruption risk next week — premium adjusted to ₹68"
No-Claim Bonus
Workers who go consecutive weeks without a claim receive a rolling discount:
Consecutive Claim-Free WeeksDiscount1–2 weeks0%3–4 weeks5%5–8 weeks10%9+ weeks20% (max)
Mid-Week Enrollment
Workers who sign up mid-week get prorated coverage from the day of signup. Premium charged = (remaining days / 7) × weekly premium.

Payment & Renewal

Auto-renewal: Every Monday via UPI AutoPay mandate (Razorpay Subscriptions)
Grace period: 24 hours if AutoPay fails — coverage remains active, worker notified
Cancellation: Worker can cancel anytime; no refund for current week's premium
Upgrade/Downgrade: Tier changes apply from next Monday
